## SERP ANALYSIS

### Competitor Summary

**Common H2 topics (baseline — not our differentiation):**
- What are cat eye nails / how the effect works
- What you need (supplies list)
- Step-by-step application
- How to use the magnet
- Tips and common mistakes
- How long they last
- Removal instructions
- FAQ block
- Best colours to try

**Content approach:** Competitors write competent but generic step-by-step walkthroughs. Most stop at the classic diagonal stripe and treat the magnet as a binary tool (hold it over, done). They treat all nail shapes and lengths as identical, avoid the physics of why things go wrong, and miss the emotional anxiety of a first DIY gel attempt entirely. Almost none address the MRI safety question despite it generating 8.6 million views on TikTok.

**Visual patterns:** Tutorial competitors use 6–10 images. Step-by-step and product shots dominate.

**Recommended image count:** 10–12 — technique variations (stripe, velvet push, galaxy swirl, French tip magnet) require visual proof at each major step.

### Competitor Gaps (Where We Win)

**Unanswered questions competitors miss:**
- Why does my effect go fuzzy or disappear — specific root causes explained mechanically (coat too thin, waited too long, cured on metal surface, re-magnetising after particles settled)
- Does nail shape affect the magnetic line — oval/almond vs short/square differences
- Can I do cat eye nails without a UV lamp — honest answer (air-dry magnetic polish exists but results are inferior)
- Do I need to remove cat eye nails before an MRI — 8.6M-view viral moment; almost no tutorials address this
- What is the difference between 5D, 8D, 9D cat eye polish — constant audience question when buying
- Can I redo the magnet if I mess up — yes, before curing; competitors rarely confirm this clearly
- Why does the base colour matter — most mention black base but few explain the contrast physics or what to do for pearl/soft effects

**Missing semantic territory:**
- Flash cure technique (brief cure to stabilise particles before full cure)
- Metal surface interference (curing on a metal table pulls particles out of alignment)
- Shake/invert bottle before application (particles sink to bottom when sitting)
- Layering technique for deeper effect (cure first coat, use magnet on second coat for extra depth)
- Nail shape effect on stripe placement — almond/oval vs short square/round differences

**Audience blind spots:**
- Beginners who already do gel at home and are adding cat eye for the first time — no tutorial speaks to this large segment specifically
- The "it's not working" troubleshooter — competitors list tips but don't diagnose why specific failures happen
- Safety context: the MRI viral moment is unaddressed in tutorial content despite massive public awareness

### Our Strategic Approach

**Differentiation:** We write for the person who already does gel nails at home and is adding cat eye for the first time — not an absolute beginner. This unlocks a more honest, technique-first voice. We give the full physics of why things go wrong, not just tips. We are the only tutorial that addresses the MRI safety question.

**Structure plan:** Open with what makes cat eye different from regular gel (just the magnet), move through supplies > base colour logic > step-by-step with technique variations > nail shape guide > troubleshooter > aftercare and safety. This covers every gap competitors miss.

**Tone direction:** Confident DIY friend who actually does her own nails — warm, technically precise, no condescension.

