- **What satisfies them:** Steps they can follow with their hands in front of them; specific numbers (2–3mm distance, 10–15 seconds, cure immediately); explanations of why each step matters; honest troubleshooting; confirmation that they can redo the magnet step if they mess up.
- **What frustrates them:** Generic tips without explanation ("work one nail at a time" with no reason why); tutorials that assume a specific magnet shape; discovering mid-manicure they needed a darker base coat; losing the effect before they can cure and not knowing why.

### Top 5 Audience Pain Points (Tutorial Intent)

